@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### Root — check model info
GET {{baseUrl}}/

###

### Single-turn chat — general question
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What is a P/E ratio and why does it matter for investors?",
  "max_tokens": 512,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

###

### Single-turn chat — custom system prompt
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Summarise the key risks of investing in tech stocks right now.",
  "system_prompt": "You are a conservative investment advisor who always highlights downside risks first.",
  "max_tokens": 400,
  "temperature": 0.5
}

###

### Multi-turn chat — conversation with history
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat/multi-turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    { "role": "system",    "content": "You are a financial analyst assistant." },
    { "role": "user",      "content": "What is a P/E ratio?" },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "A P/E ratio (Price-to-Earnings) compares a company's share price to its earnings per share. A high P/E may indicate growth expectations, while a low P/E can suggest undervaluation." },
    { "role": "user",      "content": "How does it compare to the P/B ratio?" }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 512,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

###

### Finance analysis — earnings data
POST {{baseUrl}}/analyse
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Q4 2024 results: Revenue $4.2B (up 12% YoY), Net Income $820M (up 8% YoY), Operating Margin 19.5%, Debt-to-Equity 1.4. Analyse this performance.",
  "max_tokens": 768
}

###

### Finance analysis — investment question
POST {{baseUrl}}/analyse
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "A business has a P/E of 35, revenue growth of 25% YoY, gross margin of 68%, and free cash flow of $200M on $1B revenue. Is this a good investment?",
  "max_tokens": 600
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# FILE UPLOAD ENDPOINTS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Note: replace the file paths below (< ./your-file.pdf) with actual files on your machine.
# The REST Client extension sends multipart/form-data automatically when you use this syntax.

### Universal upload — auto-detects file type (PDF / Excel / CSV / image)
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="Payment_Receipt.pdf"
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

< ./Payment_Receipt.pdf
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

Summarise this document. What are the key figures?
------Boundary--

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/pdf
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="Payment_Receipt.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Payment_Receipt.pdf
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

What are the key financial highlights and any risks mentioned?
------Boundary--

###

### Upload PDF — targeted question
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/pdf
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="annual_report.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./annual_report.pdf
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

What was the total revenue, net income, and operating margin for the most recent year?
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="max_tokens"

1024
------Boundary--

###

### Upload Excel — column sum / trend question
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/excel
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="financials.xlsx"
Content-Type: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet

< ./financials.xlsx
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

What is the total of the Revenue column? Which month had the highest profit?
------Boundary--

###

### Upload CSV — trend analysis
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/excel
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sales_data.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

< ./sales_data.csv
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

What is the overall sales trend? Are there any anomalies or months that underperformed?
------Boundary--

###

### Upload Chart / Image — trend question
### Requires: ollama pull granite3.2-vision
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/image
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="revenue_chart.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./revenue_chart.png
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

What trend does this chart show? What are the highest and lowest values visible?
------Boundary--

###

### Upload Chart — investment signal question
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/image
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="stock_chart.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./stock_chart.png
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="question"

Based on this price chart, what technical patterns are visible? Is the trend bullish or bearish?
------Boundary--

###


